Global PET Scanners Market Insights
PET Scanners Market size was valued at USD 4.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 7.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

PET Scanners Market Overview
The PET (Positron Emission Tomography) scanners market is a rapidly growing segment in the healthcare industry. It was valued at USD 5.8 billion in 2023 and is expected to reach USD 8.4 billion by 2030, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 5.4%. This growth is driven by advancements in healthcare technologies, increasing prevalence of cancer, cardiovascular diseases, and neurological disorders, as well as the rising demand for early diagnostic tools. North America holds a significant share of the market due to its advanced healthcare infrastructure and high demand for diagnostic imaging. In Asia-Pacific, the market is expected to experience strong growth due to the expansion of healthcare services in developing countries like China and India.

